oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of 114th Field Artillery Band
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: In this black and white image, the 114th Field Artillery Band is posing with their instruments on metal bleachers. The men are in their overcoats. The image is framed and there is a notation on the backing that identifies them s the HQ Company Band of the 114th Field Artillery, at Camp Sevier in 1917. The photograph belonged to Musician Kenneth Redford, HQ Co., 114th FA, 30th Div. Redford was from Franklin, Williamson County, Tennessee.
